# React Patterns

## Composition over props

- Components consume context directly via hooks — no deep prop chains
- State lives in contexts: `InvestmentContext`, `ThemeContext`
- Each context exposes a `useXxx()` hook (e.g. `useInvestment()`, `useTheme()`)

## Component rules

- Functional components only (no class components)
- No data transformation logic in components — delegate to utils or hooks
- Custom hooks for any reusable or complex logic (chart data formatting, etc.)
- Hooks grouped by domain in `hooks/` folder, one file per logical grouping
- Pages are lazy-loaded with `React.lazy()` and wrapped in `<Suspense>`

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements must have visible focus styles (`:focus-visible`)
- Use `role`, `aria-label`, `aria-checked` where appropriate
- Table headers use `scope="col"` attribute
- Navigation landmarks use proper `role` attributes
